
00:00:01,502 --> 00:00:04,872
<i>(man) TONIGHT MARK CUBAN</i>
<i>JOINS THE SHARK TANK,</i>

00:00:04,872 --> 00:00:07,374
<i>WHERE HOPEFUL ENTREPRENEURS</i>
<i>COME SEEKING AN INVESTMENT</i>

00:00:07,374 --> 00:00:09,109
<i>FROM THE SHARKS,</i>

00:00:09,109 --> 00:00:11,778
<i>FIVE POWERFUL, SELF‐MADE</i>
<i>INVESTORS WORTH BILLIONS.</i>

00:00:11,778 --> 00:00:14,248
<i>IN THE TANK,</i>
<i>THE SHARKS ARE READY TO INVEST</i>

00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:15,849
<i>USING THEIR OWN MONEY,</i>

00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:19,253
<i>BUT ONLY FOR THE RIGHT PERSON</i>
<i>WITH THE RIGHT BUSINESS.</i>

00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:21,855
WHICH ONE OF YOU SHARKS IS
READY TO INVEST IN US?

00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:24,791
<i>AND IF THE SHARKS HEAR</i>
<i>A GOOD IDEA,</i>

00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:27,294
<i>THEY'LL FIGHT EACH OTHER</i>
<i>FOR A PIECE OF IT.</i>

00:00:27,294 --> 00:00:30,030
I'M GONNA GO BACK IN.
BARBARA.

00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:32,933
ROBERT'S GIVING ME THE EYE
THAT IT'S A LOAN.
ROBERT GIVES YOU THE EYE,
BUT HE DOESN'T GIVE ANY MONEY.

00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:35,168
<i>BUT FIRST THE ENTREPRENEURS</i>
<i>MUST CONVINCE A SHARK</i>

00:00:35,168 --> 00:00:38,071
<i>TO INVEST THE FULL AMOUNT</i>
<i>THEY'RE ASKING FOR,</i>

00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:40,707
<i>OR THEY'LL WALK AWAY</i>
<i>WITH NOTHING.</i>

00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:43,710
IF I COULD EXPLAIN TO YOU GUYS
A LITTLE CLEARER‐‐
NO, JAMES,
YOU GOTTA STOP SELLING.

00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:47,080
I COULD NOT SPEAK TO YOU.
YOU TOOK FOREVER.

00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:49,349
(laughs)
BOOM GOES THE DYNAMITE!

00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:51,351
<i>WHO ARE THE SHARKS?</i>

00:00:51,351 --> 00:00:53,720
<i>KEVIN O'LEARY</i>
<i>KNOWS HOW TO MAKE MONEY.</i>

00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:56,256
<i>HE STARTED A SOFTWARE BUSINESS</i>
<i>IN HIS BASEMENT,</i>

00:00:56,256 --> 00:00:59,092
<i>WHICH HE EVENTUALLY SOLD</i>
<i>FOR $3.2 BILLION.</i>

00:00:59,092 --> 00:01:02,396
<i>BARBARA CORCORAN‐‐</i>
<i>THIS FIERY REAL ESTATE MOGUL</i>

00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,631
<i>TURNED A $1,000 LOAN</i>
<i>INTO A REAL ESTATE EMPIRE</i>

00:01:04,631 --> 00:01:06,700
<i>WORTH HUNDREDS OF MILLIONS</i>

00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:08,535
<i>IN THE SHARK‐FILLED CITY</i>
<i>OF MANHATTAN.</i>

00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:10,904
<i>DAYMOND JOHN</i>
<i>TURNED RAGS TO RICHES</i>

00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,807
<i>WITH HIS CLOTHING BRAND FUBU,</i>
<i>WHICH HAS GROSSED</i>

00:01:13,807 --> 00:01:16,243
<i>OVER $6 BILLION</i>
<i>IN WORLDWIDE RETAIL SALES.</i>

00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:17,744
<i>ROBERT HERJAVEC,</i>

00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:20,247
<i>THE SON OF A FACTORY WORKER</i>
<i>TURNED TECHNOLOGY MOGUL,</i>

00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:22,716
<i>SOLD HIS FIRST</i>
<i>INTERNET COMPANIES</i>

00:01:22,716 --> 00:01:24,251
<i>FOR OVER $350 MILLION.</i>

00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:26,186
<i>AND MARK CUBAN‐‐</i>

00:01:26,186 --> 00:01:28,922
<i>THIS SELF‐MADE BILLIONAIRE</i>
<i>STARTED OUT AS A PAPERBOY,</i>

00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,857
<i>AND NOW IS A MEDIA MOGUL</i>

00:01:30,857 --> 00:01:41,735
<i>AND THE OUTSPOKEN OWNER</i>
<i>OF THE DALLAS MAVERICKS.</i>

00:01:41,735 --> 00:01:44,004
♪♪♪

00:01:44,004 --> 00:01:46,840
<i>FIRST INTO THE SHARK TANK IS</i>
<i>JONATHAN BOOS</i>

00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:51,712
<i>WITH AN INNOVATIVE PRODUCT LINE</i>
<i>FOR THE WELL‐DRESSED MAN.</i>

00:02:02,155 --> 00:02:03,657
HI, EVERYONE.

00:02:03,657 --> 00:02:05,659
MY NAME IS JONATHAN BOOS,

00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:08,662
AND I'M THE OWNER OF
THE MEN'S BRAND WURKIN STIFFS,

00:02:08,662 --> 00:02:12,099
AS WELL AS THE INVENTOR
OF POWER STAYS,

00:02:12,099 --> 00:02:14,568
THE WORLD'S ONLY
MAGNETIC COLLAR STAYS.

00:02:14,568 --> 00:02:18,138
I'M SEEKING $85,000
FOR 10% EQUITY IN MY COMPANY.

00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:21,208
NOW THIS ALL STARTED BACK
WHEN I WAS ACTUALLY RUNNING LATE

00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:22,876
FOR SOME DINNER RESERVATIONS.

00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,712
MY WIFE WAS YELLING AS SHE THREW
A BRAND‐NEW SHIRT AT ME

00:02:25,712 --> 00:02:29,182
TO PUT ON, AND I'D SEEN
THAT I HAD A‐A BIG PROBLEM.

00:02:29,182 --> 00:02:31,685
I LOOKED LIKE JOHN TRAVOLTA
FROM "SATURDAY NIGHT FEVER."

00:02:31,685 --> 00:02:34,121
THE COLLAR WAS ALL LARGE
AND IN CHARGE,

00:02:34,121 --> 00:02:36,556
AND I COULDN'T CONTROL
THIS THING,

00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:38,759
SO I FOUND
SOME ORDINARY PAPER CLIPS,

00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,761
AND I FOUND SOME MAGNETS,

00:02:40,761 --> 00:02:43,563
AND I MADE THE VERY FIRST
MAGNETIC COLLAR STAY.

00:02:43,563 --> 00:02:45,999
I HAVEN'T WORN A SHIRT
THE SAME SINCE.

00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,502
SO FIRST YOU TAKE
OUR POWER STAY...

00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:51,371
AND YOU PLACE IT ON
THE UNDERSIDE OF THE COLLAR.

00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,473
THERE'S A COLLAR STAY POCKET.

00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:57,944
FLIP THE COLLAR DOWN,

00:02:57,944 --> 00:03:02,082
AND WE HAVE
A SUPERSTRONG, SMALL MAGNET,

00:03:02,082 --> 00:03:04,785
AND THIS GOES ON THE INSIDE
OF THE SHIRT...

00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:07,587
AND INSTANTLY CHANGED
MY SHIRT

00:03:07,587 --> 00:03:09,756
INTO
A HIDDEN BUTTON‐DOWN COLLAR.

00:03:09,756 --> 00:03:13,360
SO WHEREVER YOU PUT
YOUR COLLAR

00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,196
IS WHERE YOUR COLLAR STAYS.

00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:20,033
AND THERE'S NOTHING ELSE LIKE
THIS IN THE MENSWEAR INDUSTRY.

00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:23,503
THESE ARE SPECTACULAR.
THANK YOU. WE KNEW WE HAD
SOMETHING PRETTY SPECIAL

00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:26,506
WHEN WE ACQUIRED THREE
HIGH‐END MEN'S SPECIALTY STORES.

00:03:26,506 --> 00:03:28,675
WHAT RETAILERS
DO YOU SELL THEM IN?

00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:31,678
NORDSTROM CONTACTED US. WE DID
A TEST OF OUR POWER STAYS,

00:03:31,678 --> 00:03:33,714
WHICH LAUNCHED IN 24 STORES.

00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:36,083
WITHIN 3 MONTHS,
WE WENT TO 77 STORES.

00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,485
WE HAD SOLD
OVER 18,000 UNITS.

00:03:38,485 --> 00:03:41,288
WE MADE THEM
OVER $600,000 RETAIL.

00:03:41,288 --> 00:03:44,057
WE'RE CURRENTLY IN
ALL 115 NORDSTROM STORES.

00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:47,794
JONATHAN, YOU'RE THE REAL DEAL.
OH, YEAH.
I‐I AM THE REAL DEAL.

00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:50,430
I DESIGN AND PRODUCE
ALL THIS STUFF MYSELF.

00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:53,800
THE PACKAGING, THE DISPLAYS,
THE PRODUCT‐‐IT'S ALL ME.

00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:57,637
JONATHAN, WHAT ARE YOUR SALES
TODAY IN ALL THE PRODUCTS?

00:03:57,637 --> 00:04:00,640
THE OTHER DAY‐‐TODAY
I'M AT A HALF MILLION.

00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,810
I'M EXPECTING $1.8 MILLION
NEXT YEAR.
$1.8 MILLION? WOW.

00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:07,347
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WITH THE $85,000?
DAYMOND,
OUT OF ANYBODY HERE,

00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:09,616
YOU SHOULD KNOW‐‐
WHAT CAN I DO WITH $85,000?

00:04:09,616 --> 00:04:12,385
I MEAN, TO REALLY TAKE
THIS BRAND TO THE NEXT LEVEL,

00:04:12,385 --> 00:04:15,455
I NEED TO GET SOMEONE THAT KNOWS
WHAT THE HELL THEY'RE DOING

00:04:15,455 --> 00:04:17,457
TO GET ME THERE,
SO I CAN CONTINUE TO CREATE.

00:04:17,457 --> 00:04:19,726
I'VE GOT PRODUCTS
ON THE DRAWING BOARD.

00:04:19,726 --> 00:04:22,729
I'VE GOT PRODUCTS RIGHT NOW
STILL IN DEVELOPMENT.
JONATHAN,
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

00:04:22,729 --> 00:04:26,233
OKAY. OKAY.
I LOVE YOUR PASSION. I LOVE YOUR
KNOWLEDGE. I LOVE YOUR APPROACH.

00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:29,035
I'M WAITING FOR THE "BUT."
YEAH, THERE'S A "BUT" COMING.

00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:31,638
I'M NOT THE GUY
WITH THE CONNECTIONS.

00:04:31,638 --> 00:04:34,207
I'M NOT THE GUY
WHO ADDS VALUE.

00:04:34,207 --> 00:04:37,010
I'M JUST NOT THE GUY
TO HELP YOU. I'M OUT.

00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:40,647
JONATHAN, I JUST‐‐I REALLY CAN'T
DO ANYTHING FOR YOUR BUSINESS...
OKAY.

00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:43,216
SO I'M OUT.

00:04:43,216 --> 00:04:46,586
THE GUY THAT'S STAYING
THE MOST QUIET IS THE ONE

00:04:46,586 --> 00:04:51,491
THAT CAN HELP ME THE MOST,
BUT HE'S STAYING QUIET.
I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.

00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:56,429
I'LL GIVE YOU $100,000
FOR 30% OF THE BUSINESS, <i>BUT...</i>

00:04:56,429 --> 00:04:59,533
I WANT A ROYALTY
ON THAT MONEY.

00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,969
I WANT A 14% ROYALTY.

00:05:06,339 --> 00:05:10,343
SO IT'S LIKE A LOAN.
NO. I'M GETTING A TON OF EQUITY,
TOO. I WANT 30% OF THE COMPANY.

00:05:10,343 --> 00:05:12,078
IT'S A LOAN, RIGHT?

00:05:12,078 --> 00:05:14,347
NO, IT'S NOT A LOAN.

00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:16,950
ROBERT'S GIVING ME THE EYE
THAT IT'S A LOAN.

00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,719
(laughs)
WELL, YOU'RE PAYING 14%
OFF THE TOP. I MEAN...

00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:22,823
YOU KNOW, I LOVE ROBERT.
HE LOVES TO GIVE‐‐
I LOVE ROBERT, TOO!

00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:26,259
ROBERT GIVES YOU THE EYE,
BUT HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY MONEY.

00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:28,662
THAT'S THE PROBLEM. IN THE END,
YOU NEED CASH, MY FRIEND.

00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:31,898
I'M MAKING YOU AN OFFER.
NEVER DISRESPECT THE CASH.
DON'T LIKE THAT DEAL.

00:05:31,898 --> 00:05:33,900
YOU KNOW WHY I LIKE THAT DEAL?
BECAUSE I KNOW

00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,736
YOU'RE GONNA NEED MORE CASH.
YOU'RE GONNA BE CALLING ME

00:05:36,736 --> 00:05:38,738
EVERY 90 DAYS FOR
A QUARTER OF A MILLION DOLLARS.

00:05:38,738 --> 00:05:41,241
AND IF THINGS ARE GOING WELL,
I'LL KEEP DOING IT.

00:05:41,241 --> 00:05:43,443
BUT NOT‐‐NOT AT‐‐YEAH, YEAH.

00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:45,445
YEAH, RIGHT, EXACTLY.
ALL RIGHT. YOU HAVE AN OFFER.

00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:49,616
THAT'S ON THE TABLE.
GREAT. ANYONE ELSE?
WHY DON'T YOU LIKE HIS OFFER?

00:05:49,616 --> 00:05:52,719
I NEED MORE THAN MONEY.
I NEED SOMEONE THAT CAN HELP ME.

00:05:57,824 --> 00:06:00,694
DAYMOND, YOU‐‐YOU SOLD HATS.

00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:04,798
ONE PRODUCT, RIGHT? AND THEN YOU
CREATED THIS EMPIRE OF A BRAND.

00:06:04,798 --> 00:06:08,501
(Robert) OOH.
SO YOU'RE LOOKING AT ME
LIKE I CAN'T MAKE THIS

00:06:08,501 --> 00:06:11,905
INTO A SUCCESSFUL BRAND.
THAT'S WHAT I DON'T GET.

00:06:11,905 --> 00:06:16,042
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE COMING FROM.
I DIDN'T SAY YOU CAN'T MAKE IT
INTO A SUCCESSFUL BRAND.

00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:18,812
I‐‐
PEOPLE WHO ARE SUCCESSFUL
HAVE THOUGHTS OF HIGH VALUE,

00:06:18,812 --> 00:06:21,948
AND PEOPLE WHO ARE NOT
HAVE THOUGHTS OF LOW VALUE,

00:06:21,948 --> 00:06:25,452
SO YOU'RE VALUING YOURSELF
HIGH‐‐
HOW AM I VALUING MYSELF HIGH?
85 THOUS‐‐

00:06:25,452 --> 00:06:28,154
YOU SHOULD BE, BUT IF YOU'RE
GONNA ARGUE WITH ME...
ALL RIGHT.

00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:31,858
THEN I DON'T WANT A PARTNER
WHO'S GONNA ARGUE WITH ME...
I'M NOT‐‐I'M‐‐DAYMOND...

00:06:31,858 --> 00:06:34,628
SO JUST‐‐BECAUSE OF THAT...
YOU, OUT OF ANYBODY, SHOULD
UNDERSTAND WHAT I'M DOING.

00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:37,764
I MEAN, I DON'T‐‐
I DON'T GET IT.
I WAS ACTUALLY GONNA THROW
AN OFFER ON THE TABLE‐‐

00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:40,433
NOW HE'S GONNA SAY
BECAUSE I WAS ARGUING...
(Barbara) LET DAYMOND TALK.

00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:42,369
YOU SEE HIS HAND RIGHT THERE?

00:06:42,369 --> 00:06:45,972
I STILL AM NOT DONE TALKING.
I'M OUT.

00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:47,340
I‐I KNEW IT.

00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:51,111
JONATHAN, YOU'VE ABSOLUTELY
PISSED HIM OFF.

00:06:51,111 --> 00:06:53,546
TO CLARIFY WHAT I WAS
TRYING TO TELL YOU

00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:56,383
WAS THE REASON THAT
YOU WILL BE WEALTHY

00:06:56,383 --> 00:06:59,119
IS BECAUSE YOU HAVE
THOUGHTS OF HIGH VALUE.

00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:02,489
I WAS TRYING TO GIVE YOU
A COMPLIMENT.
OKAY.

00:07:02,489 --> 00:07:06,359
WHEN I WAS TRYING TO TALK,
I COULD NOT SPEAK TO YOU.

00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:08,962
YOU TOOK FOREVER.
I'M‐‐I'M WAITING FOR‐‐
(laughter)

00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:11,898
(Jonathan) I'M JUST SAYING...
BOOM GOES THE DYNAMITE!

00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:14,901
I'M SORRY. AND I'M SORRY, AND I
WILL NEVER TAKE FOREVER AGAIN,

00:07:14,901 --> 00:07:17,637
BECAUSE I WAS GONNA
GIVE YOU AN OFFER,

00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:20,373
AND YOU BOTCHED THE OFFER.
OH, WHAT A BABY.

00:07:20,373 --> 00:07:23,476
MY GOD.
YOU WANT ME TO GET ON
THE PHONE WITH HIM EVERY DAY?

00:07:23,476 --> 00:07:28,014
"HEY, CAN I TALK TO..."
(imitates babbling) "CLICK."
I'LL PUT IT IN THE CONTRACT
I'LL NEVER CALL YOU AGAIN.

00:07:28,014 --> 00:07:30,083
HOW'S THAT SOUND?
(laughter)

00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:33,753
I CANNOT STAND PARTNERS
THAT I CAN'T EVEN SPEAK TO.

00:07:33,753 --> 00:07:37,457
IF HE WOULD HAVE SHUT UP,
HE WOULD HAVE HAD AN OFFER.

00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:43,330
I'M GONNA APOLOGIZE, FOR REAL.
I APOLOGIZE. I DIDN'T MEAN

00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:47,100
TO COME OFF THAT WAY. IF I'VE
OFFENDED YOU IN ANY WAY...
YOU DID NOT OFFEN‐‐

00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,669
THEN I WOULD DO
NOTHING DIFFERENT.
YOU DID NOT OFFEND ME.
I'M NOT OFFENDED.

00:07:49,669 --> 00:07:51,705
MY FEELINGS AREN'T HURT‐‐
I'M‐‐I'M JUST‐‐

00:07:51,705 --> 00:07:54,741
I THINK YOU'RE MISSING OUT
ON A GREAT OPPORTUNITY.
(Barbara) COME ON, DAYMOND.

00:07:54,741 --> 00:07:57,344
YOU'RE SUCH A BABY. CUT IT OUT.
LISTEN, BARB.
I HAVE PET PEEVES. YOU DO.

00:07:57,344 --> 00:07:59,646
IF THIS IS A PET PEEVE,
GET OVER IT.

00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:03,917
WOW, YOU REALLY HURT
HIS FEELINGS, JONATHAN.
LET ME TALK TO ROBERT,
MY LAST CHANCE, AND THEN‐‐

00:08:03,917 --> 00:08:07,253
AND THEN‐‐SIT THERE AND JUST
THINK ABOUT IT. I'M A NICE GUY.

00:08:07,253 --> 00:08:10,757
THEN I'LL
STOP TALKING. OKAY.
JONATHAN, IT'S NOT THE FIRST
TIME YOU'VE HEARD THAT, IS IT?

00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:13,760
"NO"? OH, YEAH. I WOULDN'T BE
HERE IF I TOOK NO FOR AN ANSWER.

00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:17,564
NEXT.
I'M ACTUALLY UPSET.
YOU KNOW WHY? 'CAUSE I LIKE IT.

00:08:17,564 --> 00:08:20,033
WELL, AND I LIKE...
WHATEVER.

00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:23,269
SEE? (high‐pitched voice)
"WHATEVER."
I MEAN‐‐NO, I WOULD
TALK TO YOU, BUT YOU‐‐

00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:26,306
"YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK
WE SHOULD DO WITH THE COMP‐‐"

00:08:26,306 --> 00:08:29,609
(high‐pitched voice)
"WHATEVER."
NO, NO, NOT WHATEVER. DAYMOND,
I'M HERE TO... ALL RIGHT.

00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:31,878
DAYMOND, HE'S NERVOUS.
HE'S A HIGH‐ENERGY GUY.

00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:35,582
WHY DON'T YOU CUT HIM
A LITTLE SLACK?
WHY DON'T <i>YOU</i> CUT HIM A CHECK?

00:08:35,582 --> 00:08:37,817
THIS IS ALL WONDERFUL. LET'S
HOLD HANDS AND SAY "KUMBAYA."

00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:41,588
JONATHAN, DO YOU WANT
MY $100,000 OR NOT?

00:08:54,401 --> 00:08:56,870
<i>(man) JONATHAN HAS</i>
<i>AN OFFER FROM KEVIN,</i>

00:08:56,870 --> 00:09:02,175
<i>BUT THE ONE SHARK HE MOST</i>
<i>WANTED TO DEAL WITH IS OUT.</i>

00:09:02,175 --> 00:09:05,512
DO YOU WANT
MY $100,000 OR NOT?

00:09:05,512 --> 00:09:07,947
JONATHAN,
I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.

00:09:07,947 --> 00:09:12,585
I'LL GIVE YOU THE $100,000
FOR 30%, NO ROYALTY.

00:09:17,957 --> 00:09:20,460
WOULD YOU GO $200,000
FOR 30%?

00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:23,129
WAIT A SECOND. I'LL DROP
MY EQUITY ASSET DOWN.

00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:27,567
$100,000 FOR 20%, BUT I WANT
THE ROYALTY TO STAY IN PLACE.

00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:30,336
THAT'S DIFFERENT THAN
WHAT HE WANTS. HE'S A SAVAGE.

00:09:30,336 --> 00:09:33,173
HE'S ASKING FOR
A <i>THIRD</i> OF YOUR BUSINESS.

00:09:33,173 --> 00:09:35,208
YOU'RE A VULTURE!
(Mark laughs)

00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,710
BECAUSE, I MEAN, I SHOULD
BE GETTING THE ROYALTY HERE.

00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:40,914
I MEAN, I'M THE ONE
THAT'S CREATING THE STUFF.

00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:43,416
JONATHAN, I'LL GIVE YOU
$100,000 FOR 25%.

00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,685
UH, THAT'S MY FINAL OFFER.

00:09:49,689 --> 00:09:51,324
(Barbara) ONE MORE THING.

00:09:51,324 --> 00:09:53,326
I'M GONNA GO BACK IN.

00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:55,695
BARBARA!

00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:57,464
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YEAH.

00:09:57,464 --> 00:10:00,433
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU $100,000
FOR 20%,

00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:04,337
PROVIDED DAYMOND FORGIVES YOU.

00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:06,406
AND I'LL BE
YOUR FRONT MAN, DAYMOND.

00:10:06,406 --> 00:10:09,909
YOU NEVER HAVE TO TALK TO THIS
GUY. YOU JUST ENJOY HIS SUCCESS.

00:10:09,909 --> 00:10:12,045
AND YOU KNOW
I'M A GREAT FRONT MAN.

00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:16,483
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.
OH, DAYMOND.

00:10:16,483 --> 00:10:20,353
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH PERCENTAGE
