I CAN'T GET NEAR YOUR VALUATION.
DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE FOR ME.

00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,416
YET, I'M SO STUNNED BY WHAT
YOU'VE DONE... TO PEOPLE‐‐

00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:20,052
YOU GOT THEM TO SIGN
THESE CONTRACTS.

00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,755
I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.
I'LL GIVE YOU $50,000 FOR 51%.

00:20:22,755 --> 00:20:24,690
(scoffs)
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
WEAR ANKLE BRACELETS,

00:20:24,690 --> 00:20:27,693
AND EVERY TIME YOU MENTION‐‐
YOU MENTION THE WORD "DVD"?

00:20:27,693 --> 00:20:29,762
24‐VOLT SHOCK.
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS.

00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:33,399
AND YOU STAY IN THE CARS
AND YOU SIGN THOSE CONTRACTS.

00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:38,204
THE PROBLEM IS 5%, EVEN ON
A BUSINESS THAT'S GROWING.

00:20:38,204 --> 00:20:40,806
OKAY.
YOU GUYS ARE GOING TO HAVE
TO COME BACK TO ME,

00:20:40,806 --> 00:20:44,143
AND, VERY SIMPLY, IF YOU COME
BACK WITH THE RIGHT NUMBER...

00:20:44,143 --> 00:20:47,847
(Barbara) FOR $30,000?
MAN, YOU DO THIS ALL THE TIME.

00:20:47,847 --> 00:20:51,550
WELL, I THINK THE GENIUS
OF THIS WHOLE THING

00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:54,553
IS THAT YOU'VE FOUND A WAY
TO TAP INTO THE WORKING MOM

00:20:54,553 --> 00:20:57,523
<i>WHILE</i> HER KIDS
ARE AT SCHOOL.
MM‐HMM.

00:20:57,523 --> 00:21:02,094
I DON'T THINK THERE'S
A LIMIT TO WHAT YOU COULD DO.

00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:04,096
BUT I THINK
THE 5% ISN'T ENOUGH

00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,465
TO GET ME EXCITED
TO BE IN WITH YOU.

00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:08,901
OKAY.
SO I NEED
A LARGER PERCENTAGE.

00:21:08,901 --> 00:21:11,771
SO RATHER THAN ASK YOU
TO NAME A NUMBER BACK TO ME,

00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:16,442
I'M GONNA SAY THAT I'D LIKE
TO GET 20% OF YOUR BUSINESS...

00:21:16,442 --> 00:21:17,943
OKAY.

00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:20,613
FOR... WHAT? $60,000?

00:21:23,849 --> 00:21:26,952
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:30,956
UM, THANK YOU FOR YOUR OFFER,
BUT NO, THANK YOU.

00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:32,291
YOU SURE?

00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:33,893
(Mark) BEFORE YOU COME BACK‐‐

00:21:33,893 --> 00:21:37,329
ARE YOU GOING TO COME BACK
AND MAKE A COUNTER‐OFFER?
MM‐HMM.

00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:39,799
OKAY. BEFORE YOU COME BACK
WITH A COUNTEROFFER,

00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,934
HERE'S THE SCENARIO.
OKAY.

00:21:41,934 --> 00:21:45,037
I DON'T WANT TO GET INTO
A NEGOTIATION, AND A COMPETITIVE

00:21:45,037 --> 00:21:49,308
NEGOTIATION, VERSUS BARBARA,
SO IF I SAY YES TO WHATEVER

00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:52,244
YOUR COUNTER IS, YOU HAVE TO
TELL ME THAT YOU WILL SAY YES

00:21:52,244 --> 00:21:55,414
IMMEDIATELY,
AND WE HAVE A DEAL.
OKAY.

00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:56,849
I LIKE THAT. THAT'S EXCITING.

00:21:56,849 --> 00:21:59,552
I KNOW.
MY PALMS ARE SWEATING.
YES? IS THAT A YES?

00:21:59,552 --> 00:22:00,820
YES.
OKAY.

00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:04,123
OKAY. SO $100,000...
NOW WAIT A MINUTE...

00:22:04,123 --> 00:22:06,926
FOR 30%.
DONE. DONE AND DONE.

00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:09,161
CRAP.
THANK YOU AND GOOD NIGHT!

00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:12,231
(both scream)

00:22:12,231 --> 00:22:14,834
OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH.
IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

00:22:14,834 --> 00:22:16,202
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

00:22:16,202 --> 00:22:19,004
(both screaming and laughing)

00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:21,674
DID YOU LIKE THAT, BARBARA?
I DON'T LIKE IT ONE BIT.

00:22:21,674 --> 00:22:23,676
(laughs)
THAT WAS SO DAMN SMART. I‐‐

00:22:23,676 --> 00:22:25,945
NO, BUT THAT'S
A COMPLIMENT TO YOU,

00:22:25,945 --> 00:22:29,014
BECAUSE I DID NOT WANT TO GET
IN A BACK‐AND‐FORTH WITH YOU.
WELL, THANK YOU.
IT FEELS SO GOOD.

00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:32,852
"BARBARA, I SCREWED YOU,
BUT IT'S A COMPLIMENT TO YOU!"
I FEEL REALLY GOOD ABOUT IT.

00:22:32,852 --> 00:22:37,690
I'M JUST A LEAN, MEAN
SHARK MACHINE, BABY!

00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:39,191
(both scream)

00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,694
OH, MY GOSH.
WE'RE SO EXCITED.
THIS IS UNBELIEVABLE.

00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:44,196
MORE THAN WE EVER IMAGINED.
AND THEY'RE‐‐THE SHARKS,

00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:46,699
THEY'RE‐‐THEY'RE TOUGH,
BUT THEY'RE NOT THAT TOUGH.

00:22:46,699 --> 00:22:50,002
FELT GOOD ABOUT IT.
THEY GOT OUR VISION.

00:22:56,609 --> 00:23:00,913
♪♪♪

00:23:00,913 --> 00:23:03,916
I'M SHAWN DAVIS,
BETTER KNOWN AS CHEF BIG SHAKE,

00:23:03,916 --> 00:23:06,585
'CAUSE WHEN I'M IN THE KITCHEN,
I SHAKE IT LIKE THIS.

00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:10,589
(sizzling)

00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:13,993
I LEARNED HOW TO COOK GROWING UP
WITH MY ITALIAN FAMILY.

00:23:13,993 --> 00:23:17,096
YOU HEARD ME‐‐
MY ITALIAN FAMILY.

00:23:17,096 --> 00:23:20,566
I GREW UP IN A PRETTY ROUGH AREA
IN NEW YORK. AT THE AGE OF 12,

00:23:20,566 --> 00:23:23,569
MY MOTHER MADE ARRANGEMENTS FOR
ME TO MOVE IN WITH THE PALMEROS.

00:23:23,569 --> 00:23:27,106
GIOVANNI PALMERO OWNED A VERY
SUCCESSFUL ITALIAN RESTAURANT.

00:23:27,106 --> 00:23:29,375
HE TAUGHT ME EVERYTHING
ABOUT THE RESTAURANT BUSINESS.

00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:32,511
THAT'S WHERE I DEVELOPED
MY STRONG PASSION OF COOKING

00:23:32,511 --> 00:23:34,146
AND DEVELOPING FOOD PRODUCTS.

00:23:34,146 --> 00:23:37,249
NOT TOO THIN. THERE YOU GO.
LET THE KNIFE DO THE WORK.

00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:39,251
NOW I HAVE
A FAMILY OF MY OWN.

00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:41,787
IT WAS FOR MY DAUGHTER
THAT I WAS INSPIRED TO MAKE

00:23:41,787 --> 00:23:43,856
THIS HEALTHIER ALTERNATIVE
TO THE BURGER,

00:23:43,856 --> 00:23:46,025
AND THERE'S NOTHING OUT THERE
LIKE IT.

00:23:46,025 --> 00:23:47,760
C.B.S. FOODS.

00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:50,729
MY DREAM IS TO BRING
A LITTLE BIT OF CHEF BIG SHAKE

00:23:50,729 --> 00:23:52,731
TO EVERY SINGLE DINNER TABLE
ACROSS AMERICA.

00:23:52,731 --> 00:23:55,701
♪♪♪

00:24:07,646 --> 00:24:10,683
WHAT'S UP, WHAT'S UP,
WHAT'S UP, PEOPLE?

00:24:10,683 --> 00:24:13,686
MY NAME IS SHAWN DAVIS,
BETTER KNOWN AS CHEF BIG SHAKE.

00:24:13,686 --> 00:24:15,854
I'M THE PRESIDENT
OF C. B. S. FOODS.

00:24:15,854 --> 00:24:19,425
I'M HERE TODAY TO ASK
FOR $200,000

00:24:19,425 --> 00:24:23,262
IN EXCHANGE FOR 25%
OF MY BUSINESS.

00:24:23,262 --> 00:24:26,999
OUR FLAGSHIP PRODUCT IS
THE ORIGINAL SHRIMP BURGER.

00:24:26,999 --> 00:24:29,902
WE MANUFACTURE THESE BURGERS
TODAY IN FOUR DIFFERENT FLAVORS.

00:24:29,902 --> 00:24:33,405
WE HAVE
ORIGINAL, TERIYAKI, CAJUN,

00:24:33,405 --> 00:24:36,108
AND JALAPEÑO,
IF YOU LIKE IT HOT.

00:24:36,108 --> 00:24:39,945
TODAY I BROUGHT SOME SAMPLES
FOR YOU GUYS TO TRY.

00:24:42,548 --> 00:24:46,018
HEY, SHAKE,
THAT'S PRETTY GOOD.
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

00:24:46,018 --> 00:24:48,420
MMM.
TASTES GOOD.

00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:50,923
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

00:24:50,923 --> 00:24:53,926
TO DATE, WE'VE SOLD OVER
22,000 UNITS OF THESE BURGERS

00:24:53,926 --> 00:24:56,495
TO MOM‐AND‐POP STORES
AND THE RESTAURANTS.

00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:59,231
THE SALES HAVE GROSSED
RIGHT AROUND 30 GRAND.

00:24:59,231 --> 00:25:02,334
THIS YEAR, I RECOGNIZED
THE BIGGER PICTURE.

00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:04,403
MY BURGER NEEDS TO BE
IN EVERY SINGLE SUPERMARKET

00:25:04,403 --> 00:25:06,071
ACROSS AMERICA.

00:25:06,071 --> 00:25:08,073
THESE ARE THE FACTS‐‐
THE HAMBURGER BUSINESS IS

00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:10,943
A MULTIBILLION‐DOLLAR‐A‐YEAR
BUSINESS. TURKEY BURGER‐‐

00:25:10,943 --> 00:25:14,580
A BILLION‐DOLLAR‐A‐YEAR
BUSINESS.
BANKRUPTCY LAWYERS‐‐

00:25:14,580 --> 00:25:17,082
A BILLION‐DOLLAR‐A‐YEAR
BUSINESS.
(chuckles)

00:25:17,082 --> 00:25:19,918
(chuckles) C. B. S. FOODS HAS
PERFECTLY POSITIONED OURSELVES

00:25:19,918 --> 00:25:21,920
TO GROW THE SHRIMP BURGER

00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,922
TO A BILLION‐DOLLAR‐A‐YEAR
BUSINESS,

00:25:23,922 --> 00:25:26,358
JUST LIKE ITS COUNTERPARTS.

00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:30,029
WHO'S READY TO HELP ME
HELP YOU ADD SOME ZEROS

00:25:30,029 --> 00:25:33,599
TO YOUR BOTTOM LINE?
(O'Leary) SO WALK ME THROUGH
WHAT A CASE COSTS TO MAKE

00:25:33,599 --> 00:25:37,169
AND WHAT YOU SELL IT FOR.
UM, PER BURGER,
87 CENTS A BURGER.

00:25:37,169 --> 00:25:41,440
THAT'S NOT CHEAP.
AND WE RETAIL IT FOR $1.63.
IT'S PROTEIN. IT'S SHRIMP.

00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:45,077
LITTLE LIGHT
ON THE MARGINS THERE.
WELL, LET ME TELL YOU THIS.

00:25:45,077 --> 00:25:47,079
THIS IS NOT
A ONE‐DIMENSIONAL PRODUCT.

00:25:47,079 --> 00:25:50,783
YOU'RE BUYING A BRAND.
YOU'RE BUYING C. B. S. FOODS.
WE'RE BUYING SHAWN.

00:25:50,783 --> 00:25:53,952
YOU'RE BUYING
CHEF BIG SHAKE.
AND WHAT OTHER PRODUCTS
ARE UNDER C. B. S.?

00:25:53,952 --> 00:25:56,789
THE LOBSTER SLIDER, WHICH
THEY'VE TAKEN 300 CASES OF.

00:25:56,789 --> 00:25:59,491
COLLECTIVELY, ALL OF MY MARGINS,
ALL PUT TOGETHER,

00:25:59,491 --> 00:26:02,394
ALL OF OUR PRODUCTS,
IS RUNNING RIGHT AROUND 63%.

00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,963
HOW IS THIS BUSINESS WORTH
$800,000 TODAY?

00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:06,965
YOU'VE ONLY GOT $30,000
IN SALES.

00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:10,169
YOU'RE NOT MAKING ANY MONEY.
WHAT I HAVE IS COMMITMENTS

00:26:10,169 --> 00:26:13,806
FROM TWO SUPERMARKETS
THAT SAID TO ME‐‐

00:26:13,806 --> 00:26:16,408
THEY FLEW ME IN AFTER TASTING
EXACTLY WHAT YOU TASTED

00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:18,911
AND SAID, "YOU KNOW WHAT?
WE WANT YOU IN HERE."

00:26:18,911 --> 00:26:22,014
SO THESE ARE ONLY
2 SUPERMARKETS OUT OF 32,000

00:26:22,014 --> 00:26:24,817
ACROSS THIS COUNTRY.
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE THAT ORDER.

00:26:24,817 --> 00:26:27,853
I WILL HAVE THIS ORDER
WITHIN THE NEXT TEN DAYS.
AND THAT ORDER WILL BE HOW BIG?

00:26:27,853 --> 00:26:31,056
FOR THE BURGERS, 600 CASES,
AND FOR THE SLIDERS, 300 CASES.

00:26:31,056 --> 00:26:33,692
WHAT WOULD THE DOLLAR AMOUNT
OF THOSE ORDERS BE?

00:26:33,692 --> 00:26:35,327
$87,200.

00:26:35,327 --> 00:26:39,298
SO YOU'VE GOT $30,000
IN SALES THIS YEAR.
YES.

00:26:39,298 --> 00:26:42,234
LET'S SAY IT'S $100,000
IN ORDERS THIS YEAR.
OKAY. OKAY.

00:26:42,234 --> 00:26:44,503
HOW MUCH MONEY WILL YOU MAKE
ON $100,000?

00:26:44,503 --> 00:26:48,340
I WOULD MAKE ROUGHLY 53%.

00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,842
(sighs)

00:26:49,842 --> 00:26:52,311
(Mark) MAN, I'VE GOTTA SAY,
I LIKE THE CONCEPT.

00:26:52,311 --> 00:26:55,948
YOU'VE GOT A CUSTOMER IN ME.
I'LL‐‐I'LL BUY THE PRODUCT.

00:26:55,948 --> 00:26:59,818
BUT I REALLY CAN'T ADD VALUE.
I DON'T KNOW THE FOOD BUSINESS.

00:26:59,818 --> 00:27:02,821
I'M GONNA HAVE TO SAY
THAT I'M OUT.

00:27:02,821 --> 00:27:05,023
(Barbara)
AND, SHAWN, I HAVE TO SAY,

00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:07,259
I JUST DON'T LIKE SHRIMP AT ALL,

00:27:07,259 --> 00:27:09,361
SO I'M JUST GOING OUT
ON THAT BASIS.

00:27:09,361 --> 00:27:11,997
(O'Leary) YOU AND I ARE
ACTUALLY DOING BUSINESS

00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:15,534
TOGETHER RIGHT NOW.
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW IT.

00:27:15,534 --> 00:27:19,338
I OWN THE DEBT OF ONE
OF THE LARGEST MANUFACTURERS

00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:21,940
OF CRUSTACEAN AND PROTEINS
OFF THE BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN.

00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:24,610
I ALWAYS KNEW YOU WERE
A BOTTOM‐FEEDER, KEVIN.

00:27:24,610 --> 00:27:27,246
SHAWN, MY CONCERN
IS YOUR MARGINS...

00:27:27,246 --> 00:27:29,381
YES, SIR.
AREN'T HIGH ENOUGH.

00:27:29,381 --> 00:27:32,384
THEY HAVE TO BE NORTH OF 70%
IN SEAFOOD, BECAUSE IT REQUIRES

00:27:32,384 --> 00:27:34,820
A HEAVY COMMITMENT
TO REFRIGERATION AND STORAGE

00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,823
AND ALSO ACCESS TO SUPPLY
OF THE PROTEIN YOU'RE USING,

00:27:37,823 --> 00:27:40,325
WHICH IS
THE MOST EXPENSIVE FOOD WE EAT

00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:43,896
AND THE MOST VULNERABLE TO
PRICE INCREASES AND DECREASES.

00:27:43,896 --> 00:27:46,498
SO AT THE END OF THE DAY,

00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:48,967
UM, TO ME, WHILE IT'S
AN INTERESTING FOOD CONCEPT,

00:27:48,967 --> 00:27:51,470
IT'S PROBABLY
ONE OF THE MORE RISKY,

00:27:51,470 --> 00:27:53,672
AND, UH,
FOR THAT REASON, I'M OUT.

00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:57,242
OKAY. OKAY.

00:27:57,242 --> 00:27:59,545
(Robert)
SHAWN, I LOVE THE PRODUCT.

00:27:59,545 --> 00:28:01,914
$200,000 FOR YOUR COMPANY‐‐

00:28:01,914 --> 00:28:05,184
I DON'T THINK
YOUR WHOLE COMPANY IS WORTH

00:28:05,184 --> 00:28:07,452
$200,000 TO $300,000 TODAY.

00:28:07,452 --> 00:28:10,856
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BUILD IT

00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:14,293
AND IT'S GONNA BE SUCCESSFUL.
THIS IS NOT
A ONE‐DIMENSIONAL PRODUCT.

00:28:14,293 --> 00:28:16,395
THESE ARE SHRIMP BURGERS.
AMERICA LOVES SHRIMP.

00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:18,864
IT'S THE NUMBER ONE
SEAFOOD PRODUCT.

00:28:18,864 --> 00:28:21,366
I LOVE THE SHRIMP.
I HATE THE VALUATION.

00:28:21,366 --> 00:28:23,602
THE COMPANY
ISN'T WORTH THAT TODAY.

00:28:23,602 --> 00:28:25,637
FOR THAT REASON, UH, I'M OUT.

00:28:25,637 --> 00:28:27,573
OKAY.

00:28:27,573 --> 00:28:29,341
<i>(man) FOUR SHARKS ARE OUT.</i>

00:28:29,341 --> 00:28:31,710
<i>DAYMOND JOHN IS</i>
<i>SHAWN'S LAST CHANCE</i>

00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:33,712
<i>TO MAKE A DEAL.</i>

00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:36,014
DAYMOND?

00:28:36,014 --> 00:28:39,685
I LIKED THOSE BURGERS. I‐‐
LOOK, I ATE 'EM. BOTH OF 'EM.

00:28:39,685 --> 00:28:43,088
AND I'M GONNA EAT THE OTHER
GUYS' BURGERS WHEN THEY LEAVE.

00:28:43,088 --> 00:28:46,091
(sighs) I CAN'T GET AROUND
THE NUMBER THAT YOU'RE ASKING.

00:28:46,091 --> 00:28:48,594
YOU'RE VALUATING
YOUR COMPANY AT $800,000.

00:28:48,594 --> 00:28:52,364
I CAN'T GET AROUND IT,
SO I HAVE TO SAY...

00:28:52,364 --> 00:28:54,933
WELL, I'M WILLING TO‐‐
I'M WILLING TO...

00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:58,570
INCREASE THE PERCENTAGE
TO BUY INTO MY COMPANY.

00:29:01,273 --> 00:29:04,710
I'M WILLING TO DO THAT.

00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:06,545
WHAT PERCENTAGE?

00:29:06,545 --> 00:29:09,414
I'M WILLING TO GO UP TO 30%.

00:29:09,414 --> 00:29:12,918
YOU HAVE SOMEBODY WHO'S
PASSIONATE ABOUT THE PRODUCT.

00:29:12,918 --> 00:29:15,587
YOU HAVE SOMEBODY
WHO LOVES THIS BUSINESS.

00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:18,257
YOU HAVE SOMEBODY
WHO STUDIED THIS BUSINESS.

00:29:18,257 --> 00:29:21,793
I HAVE THE STRONG PASSION
AND KNOW HOW TO DO IT.

00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:31,069
WHAT IF I OFFER 40%
OF THE COMPANY?

00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,542
EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU IS RIGHT
EXCEPT FOR THAT NUMBER,

00:29:37,542 --> 00:29:40,145
AND YOU'RE NOW AT 40%
FOR $200,000,

00:29:40,145 --> 00:29:43,081
SO NOW YOU'RE VALUATING
THE COMPANY AT ABOUT...

00:29:43,081 --> 00:29:44,883
ROUGHLY $570,000.
$500,000.

00:29:44,883 --> 00:29:46,952
YES, SIR. $500,000.

00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:50,255
I'D BE BUYING MORE INTO YOU
'CAUSE YOU'RE A GREAT GUY

00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:53,592
THAN BUYING
INTO THE BUSINESS...

00:29:53,592 --> 00:29:55,327
SO... I'M OUT.

00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,934
THANK YOU.

00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:09,174
(O'Leary)
EVEN IF HE HAS THOSE ORDERS,

00:30:09,174 --> 00:30:12,644
THE BUSINESS IS NOT WORTH
$500,000.
NO, BUT HE DID HAVE
A BUSINESS.

00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:16,181
YOU KNOW, HE'S‐‐
HE'LL GET THERE.
I HOPE HE REALLY MAKES IT.

00:30:16,181 --> 00:30:17,683
WELL, WHEN I GET HOME

00:30:17,683 --> 00:30:20,185
AND TELL MY FAMILY THAT
I DIDN'T GET THE INVESTMENT,

00:30:20,185 --> 00:30:22,287
I THINK INITIALLY THEY'RE GONNA
BE A LITTLE DISAPPOINTED,

00:30:22,287 --> 00:30:24,289
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?
EVERYTHING HAPPENS FOR A REASON.

00:30:24,289 --> 00:30:26,358
THIS IS NOT GONNA STOP.

00:30:26,358 --> 00:30:29,294
I HAVE A STRONG SUPPORT SYSTEM,
AND I KNOW THEY'LL BE THERE,

00:30:29,294 --> 00:30:32,297
AND WE'RE GONNA KEEP CONTINUING
MOVING FORWARD.

00:30:39,805 --> 00:30:41,173
♪♪♪

00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:43,809
(man)
MY NAME IS JAMES MARTIN.

00:30:43,809 --> 00:30:46,244
I LIVE IN
BEAUTIFUL OREGON WINE COUNTRY,

00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:48,914
AND MY PRODUCT IS COPA DI VINO.

00:30:48,914 --> 00:30:51,616
I COME FROM A FAMILY
OF CHERRY FARMERS,

00:30:51,616 --> 00:30:55,187
AND MY FAMILY HAS LIVED HERE
FOR SEVEN GENERATIONS.

00:30:55,187 --> 00:30:57,356
I WORKED
IN THE WORLD OF TECHNOLOGY

00:30:57,356 --> 00:30:59,925
AND THEN MOVED BACK
TO THE SMALL COMMUNITY

00:30:59,925 --> 00:31:02,928
TO TRY TO RAISE A FAMILY
ON THE FARM

00:31:02,928 --> 00:31:05,697
AND BECAME PASSIONATE
ABOUT WINE,

00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:07,699
WHICH IS
AN AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT,

00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:10,035
AND DEVELOPED MY OWN WINERY.

00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:11,536
COPA! HEY!

00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:14,906
COPA DI VINO WILL MAKE WINE
EASIER AND MORE ACCESSIBLE

00:31:14,906 --> 00:31:16,842
FOR PEOPLE TO ENJOY.

00:31:16,842 --> 00:31:20,946
OUR TECHNOLOGY ALLOWS WINEMAKERS
TO BE ABLE TO PACKAGE WINE

00:31:20,946 --> 00:31:24,149
IN A WAY THAT THEY'VE NEVER
BEEN ABLE TO BEFORE.

